* Blender not installed or too old
  Install the `blender` package, i.e.: `sudo apt-get install blender`
  - Mandatory for `blender_export`

* KiCad PCB/SCH Diff not installed or too old
  Visit: https://github.com/INTI-CMNB/KiDiff
  Download it from: https://github.com/INTI-CMNB/KiDiff/releases
  This tool might be automatically downloaded by KiBot.
  - Mandatory for: `diff`, `kiri`

* Pandoc not installed or too old
  Install the `pandoc` package, i.e.: `sudo apt-get install pandoc`
  You should also install the following packages: texlive, texlive-latex-base, texlive-latex-recommended
  In CI/CD environments: the `kicad_auto_test` docker image contains it.
  - Optional to create PDF/ODF/DOCX files for `report`

* Python module `ReportLab` not installed, too old or incompatible
  Install the `python3-reportlab` package, i.e.: `sudo apt-get install python3-reportlab`
  - Optional to create a PDF with BoM labels for `bom_labels`

* Python module `ZStd` not installed, too old or incompatible
  Install the `python3-zstd` package, i.e.: `sudo apt-get install python3-zstd`
  - Optional to copy embedded files from the schematic to the KiCad cache for general use

